APPENDIX B: UNIVERSAL DOCKING STANDARD (UDS) – DRAFT TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION V1.0

B.1 Scope and Purpose
This specification defines the mechanical, fluid, electrical, and data interfaces required for the interconnection of modular Starship-derived habitats on the Martian surface. Compliance ensures interoperability, safety, and automated connection capability.

B.2 Mechanical Interface

· Designation: UDS-Mech-100.
· Geometry: Circular interface, 2.5m diameter.
· Connection System: Androgynous, semi-kinematic capture latch system. Allows for ±15 cm misalignment and ±5° angular error.
· Seal: Dual redundant silicone-Kevlar gaskets, creating an interstitial volume for leak detection.
· Load Bearing: Designed to transfer axial and shear loads between modules, accommodating thermal expansion and settling.

B.3 Fluid Transfer Interfaces

· UDS-Fluid-A: Breathable Air. 2x ports (N₂/O₂ mix). Quick-disconnect, self-sealing. Pressure: 50 psi max.
· UDS-Fluid-B: Potable Water. 2x ports. Quick-disconnect, self-sealing. Material: Stainless steel, bacteriostatic lining.
· UDS-Fluid-C: Thermal Transfer Fluid. 2x ports (Glycol-water mix). Insulated, high-flow couplers.
· UDS-Fluid-D: Utility Gas/Vacuum. 2x ports (CO₂, CH₄, O₂, or vacuum). Color-coded for specific service.

B.4 Electrical & Data Interfaces

· UDS-Power: 480 VDC, 500 A max. High-current connector with electromagnetic latching. Polarity keyed.
· UDS-Data-Optical: 12-fiber MT connector for high-bandwidth comms (settlement LAN).
· UDS-Data-Controller: Ruggedized Ethernet connector for control systems (CAN bus protocol).

B.5 Connection Protocol Sequence

1. Approach: Robotic rover aligns modules via visual targets/LiDAR.
2. Mechanical Capture: UDS-Mech-100 latches engage.
3. Seal Pressurization: Interstitial volume pressurized and monitored for leaks.
4. Service Connection: Robotic actuator sequentially mates fluid and electrical connectors.
5. Handshake: Linked modules exchange system status and confirm green status.
6. Tunnel Pressurization: Interior pressure door opens, establishing shirt-sleeve connection.

