C.3 Analysis
This budget reveals a critical challenge: a fully outfitted Habitation Starship exceeds the nominal 150t payload. This necessitates:

1. Redesign/De-scoping: Reducing consumables buffer, leveraging more commonality with other ships.
2. Dual Landing Strategy: The MVH suite and critical systems land in one ship; bulk water shielding and non-critical furnishings land in a dedicated "Logistics" Starship for later connection.
   This exercise validates the necessity of the detailed fleet-level mass modeling advocated in Chapter 4.

